Unless required otherwise (e.g. if I say "no test"), ALWAYS test thoroughly (but not redundantly) before you modify existing scripts or create target scripts:
1. make a TEST_{purpose} (**in snake_case**) folder under the current working directory. make copies of target scripts to start if it makes things smoother.
2. write tests for every orthogonal aspect of the modification or addition, remember to add all necessary logging for your own feedback.
3. run and update the test code until tests pass, then edit target script.
4. repeat the process until the all scripts are working as expected.
5. run comprehensive tests on the entire workflow to ensure everything is working as expected.
6. after everthing works as expected, write **one and only summary document** into the `./DOC/` folder under the current working directory, including but not limited to: a. complete user guidance, b. overall workflow, c. key code snippets and explanations.
7. finally, tell me which TEST_{purpose} folder should I retrospect.

Whenever you are not sure what to test, ask me for help.